  "text": "The most wonderful time of year looks different for everyone. For some, it’s the Christmas holiday season. However, ask any beauty enthusiast and editor, and they’ll likely collectively respond with the same answer: Black Friday and Cyber Monday. Several brands use the few days after Thanksgiving to treat their bestselling SKUs to a hefty discount, and one brand high on beauty wishlists is the UK-beloved Medik8.Medik8, a popular British skin care brand, has rapidly gained recognition among industry experts, beauty editors, and dedicated skin care enthusiasts. Although the advent of a skin care brand isn’t always well-received, Medik8’s presence has been met with praise, particularly for its effective Crystal Retinal collection, plumping Liquid Peptides, and the ELLE-approved Super C Ferulic. Each product under the brand’s umbrella combines clinical and consumer research to bring you the best-in-class ingredients straight from the company’s in-house lab. If Medik8 has ever been on your radar, its Black Friday and Cyber Monday sales present the perfect opportunity to take the British skin care brand for a spin. Starting November 24 to December 3, Medik8 is offering 30 percent off all full-sized products—yes, that includes the aforementioned formulas, as well as other standouts like the Lipid Balance Cleansing Oil, Ultimate Recovery Bio-Cellulose Mask, and Crystal Retinal Eye Cream. Additionally, if you spend over $140, you’ll get a complimentary travel-sized Hydr8 B5 Intense and C-Tetra Luxe. The discount is not offered on any skin bundles or accessories.To help you cut through the noise, we compiled a list of the best Medik8 products to shop during the Black Friday and Cyber Monday sale. Your skin will thank you. Medik8 Liquid Peptides™Medik8 Crystal RetinalMedik8 Total Moisture Daily Facial CreamNow 30% OffMedik8 Press \u0026 Glow®Now 30% OffMedik8 Super C FerulicMedik8 Surface Radiance CleanseNerisha Penrose is the Beauty Commerce Editor at ELLE.com. Prior to joining the team, she was an Editorial Fellow at ELLE.com. In her current role, she helps lead coverage on makeup, skin care, hair, and fragrances. With over six years of experience in the world of beauty editorial, Nerisha enjoys delving deep into the complexities of fragrance notes, hunting for the best fixes for acne-prone skin, and advocating for daily sunscreen use. She regularly researches and tests the latest products, consults beauty professionals (including our Beauty Advisory Board) to determine the best expert-approved formulas to recommend, and conducts interviews with luminaries across the industry. Nerisha received her bachelor’s degree in Communication and Media Studies from Temple University before joining the editorial teams at Nylon and Billboard. In 2020, she co-launched our popular franchise The State of Black Beauty, an ongoing exploration of—and destination for—beauty at the intersection of Black culture.",
